A hand-pleated, hand-cut, spiked flower dress in dégradé flax flower blue silk gauze organza.

The flax flower is violet blue in colour, ephemeral - in bloom for only hours.

The linen farm is dedicated to the growing of flax and, with that, the regeneration of wildlife and the drawing together of the local community.

Photographed at the Paris atelier at the Spring/Summer 2020 show by @ChloeLeDrezen.

A moonshine blue Irish linen dress, first constructed as a paper doll by the design team.

The dress was hand embroidered in the atelier with continuous, spontaneous sketches of dancing girls drawn by Central Saint Martins MA students.

The sketches were created during a life drawing class held at the Alexander McQueen educational space, at #27OldBondStreet.

Photographed by @_AdamaJalloh and @ChloeLeDrezen in the Paris atelier.

The swirling red Rose dress from the AW19 collection.

The silhouette was initially draped on the house model by Sarah Burton and her studio team.

The techniques needed to capture the abundant asymmetry of a natural rose were devised with Sarah and Judy Halil, Head of the Atelier, in an intensive process of pin-tucking in the neckline and free-form gathering of whorls in the volume of the skirt.

#McQueenRoses at #27OldBondStreet, our London flagship.

Photographed by @chloeledrezen.
